name: Unidentified_clone_commando
content:
A clone commando operated under the Galactic Empire during the early days of the Imperial Era. As the Imperial Military transitioned from clones to conscription forces under Project War-Mantle, this clone commando was sent along with other commandos to the Imperial Base on Daro to train non-clone human soldiers as replacements for the clone troopers. The base was infiltrated by Clone Force 99 around 19 BBY, shortly after Clone Captain CC-5576 "Gregor" was arrested for desertion. This commando attempted to prevent the renegade clone squad from escaping through the facility's thermal exhaust port, but was shot by friendly fire by a group of TK troopers. The commando took several blaster shots to the chest and consequently fell to the planet's surface.
The clone commando wore Katarn-class Commando Armor and was armed with a DC-15A blaster carbine.
The clone commando first appeared in "War-Mantle," the fourteenth episode of Star Wars: The Bad Batch. He was voiced by Dee Bradley Baker.
